      • fireSubCommand

        boolean fireSubCommand(org.bukkit.command.CommandSender sender,
                       String[] a)
        Takes the root command arguments and processes it into a new sub-command (first argument). The rest are passed as arguments to a resolved sub command. If no sub command is found, false is returned.
        Parameters:
        sender - the command sender
        a - the arguments of the super-command
        Returns:
        true if a command was executed, false otherwise
